            "summary": "Kids find a scarab amulet at an archaeology dig that transports them",
            "text": "The summer sun beats down on the excavation site in Egypt. {{PLAYER1_NAME}} and {{PLAYER2_NAME}} are here with their uncle Ahmed, an archaeologist who studies ancient Egypt.\n\n'Careful now,' Uncle Ahmed warns as they help brush sand from a newly discovered chamber. 'This tomb hasn't been opened in three thousand years.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}}'s brush uncovers something glinting in the sand‚Äîa golden scarab beetle amulet, its surface carved with hieroglyphics.\n\n'Extraordinary!' Uncle Ahmed breathes. 'Don't touch it yet, let me get my‚Äî'\n\nBut {{PLAYER1_NAME}} has already picked it up. The scarab feels warm, almost alive. Suddenly, the world spins. Sand swirls around them like a golden tornado.\n\nWhen it settles, they're standing in the same desert‚Äîbut everything has changed. The excavation site is gone. In its place rises a massive stone structure, not quite finished, swarming with thousands of workers.\n\n'The Great Pyramid,' {{PLAYER2_NAME}} gasps. 'It's... it's being built!'",
