            "summary": "The scarab bears the name of Pharaoh Khufu and a riddle",
            "text": "{{PLAYER1_NAME}} studies the scarab closely. The hieroglyphics are tiny but precise. Uncle Ahmed taught them some basics of reading ancient Egyptian writing.\n\n'This cartouche‚Äîthe oval shape‚Äîthat's a royal name,' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} says. 'I think it says... Khufu?'\n\n'Pharaoh Khufu!' {{PLAYER2_NAME}} remembers. 'He built the Great Pyramid of Giza!'\n\nBelow the name, more symbols: a sun disk, a bird, what looks like water ripples.\n\n'It's some kind of riddle,' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} realizes. 'The sun... crosses the sky each day... like a bird... over the waters of the Nile?'\n\nThe scarab pulses with warmth. More symbols appear, glowing faintly: 'THE SEEKER WHO UNDERSTANDS THE JOURNEY OF RA SHALL FIND THE PATH HOME.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} looks at the massive pyramid rising in the distance. 'Ra was the sun god. The Egyptians believed he traveled across the sky each day. I think we need to learn about their beliefs to get home.'",
