            "summary": "They meet a priest who mistakes them for divine messengers",
            "text": "A man in white linen robes approaches them. His head is shaved, and he carries a staff topped with a golden sun disk. His eyes widen when he sees them.\n\n'Strange visitors! Your clothes... your manner... you are not from any land I know.' He studies them intently. 'I am Meru, priest of Ra at Heliopolis. The gods have sent you, have they not?'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} holds up the glowing scarab. 'We found this. It brought us here, but we don't know why.'\n\nMeru's expression shifts to wonder. 'The Scarab of Awakening! It was lost centuries ago. It is said to choose those destined to learn the wisdom of Egypt.' He bows his head. 'You are guests of the gods. I will teach you what you seek to know.'\n\nHe gestures toward the river, where boats glide past temples and gardens. 'What would you learn? The secrets of the pyramids? The mystery of the afterlife? The writing of the gods? I am at your service.'",
