        "pyramid-construction": {
            "id": "pyramid-construction",
            "summary": "They witness the incredible engineering of pyramid building",
            "text": "Up close, the pyramid construction is even more impressive. Thousands of workers haul massive limestone blocks on wooden sledges. Others pour water on the sand to help the sledges glide.\n\nA foreman notices them staring. 'First time seeing the work, young ones? Pharaoh's tomb will stand for eternity!'\n\n'How do you move such huge stones?' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} asks.\n\n'Teamwork, ramps, and the blessing of the gods!' He points to a long ramp spiraling up the pyramid's side. 'Each block weighs as much as two elephants. Twenty men pull each sledge. We cut the stones at the quarry, float them down the Nile on boats, then drag them here.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} does mental math. 'There must be millions of blocks!'\n\n'Two million, three hundred thousand,' the foreman says proudly. 'And every one placed precisely. The base is level within a finger's width across the entire foundation. The sides align perfectly with the four directions‚Äînorth, south, east, west.'\n\n'How do you get them so precise without modern tools?'\n\n'The stars guide us. We sight the north star for direction. Water levels and plumb bobs ensure straightness. Knowledge is our tool.'",
