        "pyramid-workers": {
            "id": "pyramid-workers",
            "summary": "They learn that pyramid builders were skilled workers, not slaves",
            "text": "'Are these workers... slaves?' {{PLAYER2_NAME}} asks hesitantly.\n\nThe foreman looks offended. 'Slaves? No! These are skilled craftsmen, the finest in Egypt. They choose to serve Pharaoh. In return, they receive food, beer, shelter, medical care, and the honor of building eternity.'\n\nHe leads them to a workers' village nearby. 'See? These are not hovels. The builders live well. They work in rotating teams‚Äîthree months on, then home to their farms for harvest. Bakers make fresh bread daily. Doctors tend injuries. Scribes record every worker's contribution so their names live forever.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} sees workers laughing, eating lunch in the shade, playing a game that looks like checkers. 'They seem... happy?'\n\n'Building Pharaoh's tomb is sacred work. When he ascends to join the gods, he will remember those who helped him. Their families will be honored for generations. This is not punishment‚Äîthis is purpose.'\n\nAn old man nearby adds, 'My grandfather helped build Pharaoh Sneferu's pyramid. My grandson will tell his grandchildren about this one. We are part of something eternal.'",
