        "pyramid-purpose": {
            "id": "pyramid-purpose",
            "summary": "They learn pyramids are resurrection machines for the pharaoh",
            "text": "Meru the priest finds them at the pyramid site. 'I see you are curious about the great tomb. Come, I will explain its true purpose.'\n\nHe leads them to a quiet spot overlooking the construction. 'The pyramid is not merely a grave. It is a machine‚Äîa machine for resurrection.'\n\n'Resurrection?' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} asks.\n\n'When Pharaoh dies, his body is preserved through mummification. His spirit‚Äîhis Ka‚Äîremains near the body, but his soul‚Äîhis Ba‚Äîmust journey through the underworld. If he succeeds, he joins the sun god Ra, reborn each morning.'\n\nMeru points to the pyramid's sloping sides. 'See the angle? The pyramid is a ray of sunlight, solidified in stone. The chambers inside align with certain stars. When the Ba rises from the body, it travels up through the pyramid, following the starlight, joining the eternal sky.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} stares at the massive structure with new understanding. 'It's not just a tomb. It's... a launch pad?'\n\n'In a manner of speaking,' Meru smiles. 'A bridge between earth and heaven.'",
