        "pyramid-secrets": {
            "id": "pyramid-secrets",
            "summary": "Meru reveals the mathematical precision hidden in the pyramids",
            "text": "Meru leads them to a chamber where architects pore over papyrus plans. 'The pyramids are built on sacred mathematics,' he explains. 'Numbers given to us by the god Thoth himself.'\n\nHe shows them calculations scratched on limestone. 'The height of the Great Pyramid, multiplied by one million, gives the distance from Earth to the Sun. The perimeter, divided by twice the height, gives a number we call the Circle Ratio‚Äîwhat you might call pi.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}}'s jaw drops. 'They knew about pi?'\n\n'We did not call it that. But we understood circles, spheres, the relationships between shapes. How else could we build so precisely?'\n\nHe traces more figures. 'The base is aligned to true north within one-fifteenth of a degree. We measured this using the stars. The Egyptians were astronomers long before we were builders.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} realizes something. 'So the pyramids aren't just big. They're... smart. Packed with knowledge.'\n\n'The stones will crumble someday,' Meru says. 'But the mathematics within them? That is truly eternal.'",
