        "afterlife-beliefs": {
            "id": "afterlife-beliefs",
            "summary": "Meru explains the journey of the soul through the underworld",
            "text": "Meru leads them to a temple, its walls covered with colorful paintings. 'The afterlife is not simple rest,' he explains. 'It is a journey‚Äîthe most important journey of all.'\n\nHe points to painted scenes. 'When you die, your Ba‚Äîyour soul‚Äîdescends into the Duat, the underworld. There, you face trials and monsters. You must answer riddles from gatekeepers. You must recite spells from the Book of the Dead to protect yourself.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} studies a painting of a jackal-headed figure. 'Who is that?'\n\n'Anubis, god of mummification. He guides souls to the Hall of Judgment, where your heart is weighed against the feather of Ma'at‚Äîtruth and justice. If your heart is light‚Äîif you lived a good, honest life‚Äîyou pass through to the Field of Reeds, paradise. But if your heart is heavy with evil...'\n\nHe points to a creature with a crocodile head, lion body, and hippo hindquarters. 'Ammit the Devourer eats your soul. You cease to exist. Forever.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} shivers. 'So living a good life isn't just about now. It's about later too.'",
