        "mummification": {
            "id": "mummification",
            "summary": "They learn the complex 70-day process of preserving bodies",
            "text": "'Why preserve the body?' {{PLAYER2_NAME}} asks. 'If the soul travels to paradise, why does the body matter?'\n\n'The Ka‚Äîyour life force‚Äîstays with the body,' Meru explains. 'It needs a home to return to. Without a preserved body, the Ka becomes homeless, wandering, lost. The mummy anchors you to both worlds.'\n\nHe describes the process. 'Mummification takes seventy days. First, we remove the internal organs‚Äîthe lungs, liver, stomach, and intestines. These are preserved in special jars. The heart stays in the body; you'll need it for judgment.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} grimaces. 'What about the brain?'\n\n'Removed through the nose with special hooks. We didn't think the brain was important‚Äîto us, the heart was the seat of thought and feeling.'\n\nHe continues: 'The body is covered in natron salt for forty days to dry it out. Then it's wrapped in hundreds of yards of linen bandages, with protective amulets placed between the layers. Prayers are spoken at each step.'\n\n'That's a lot of work,' {{PLAYER2_NAME}} observes.\n\n'Eternity deserves careful preparation.'",
