        "egyptian-gods": {
            "id": "egyptian-gods",
            "summary": "Meru introduces the major Egyptian gods and their roles",
            "text": "Meru leads them through a gallery of statues. 'Our gods are many, each with their own domain.'\n\n'Ra, the sun god, is king of all. Each day he sails across the sky in his solar boat, bringing light. Each night he journeys through the underworld, battling chaos, to be reborn at dawn. The cycle never ends.'\n\nHe points to others. 'Osiris, god of the dead and resurrection. He was killed by his jealous brother Set, but his wife Isis brought him back. He rules the underworld now, judging souls.'\n\n'Horus, the falcon-headed god, son of Osiris. He represents the living pharaoh. When a pharaoh dies, he becomes Osiris; when a new one rises, he becomes Horus.'\n\n'Thoth, the ibis-headed god of wisdom and writing. He invented hieroglyphics and keeps records of all knowledge.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} notices something. 'They all have animal heads but human bodies. Why?'\n\n'Animals embody divine qualities. Falcons see far‚Äîlike the vision of a king. Ibises wade through murky water finding food‚Äîlike scholars finding truth. Jackals guard the dead. The gods are both like us and beyond us.'",
