        "hieroglyphics-lesson": {
            "id": "hieroglyphics-lesson",
            "summary": "A scribe teaches them the basics of hieroglyphic writing",
            "text": "Meru introduces them to a scribe named Khaemwaset. 'He has trained since age four in the House of Life. He can teach you our sacred writing.'\n\nKhaemwaset shows them a papyrus scroll covered in tiny pictures. 'Hieroglyphics are not mere pictures. They are sounds and ideas combined. This owl'‚Äîhe points‚Äî'represents the sound M. This water ripple is N. This foot is B.'\n\n'So you spell things out phonetically?' {{PLAYER2_NAME}} asks.\n\n'Sometimes. But some symbols represent whole words or concepts. This eye is the Eye of Horus‚Äîprotection and health. This ankh is life itself. Skilled readers know when to sound out and when to recognize.'\n\nHe hands them reed brushes and ink. 'Write your names. Sound them out, find the symbols.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} slowly constructs {{PLAYER1_HIS_HER}} name, symbol by symbol. It's hard‚Äîthere are over 700 hieroglyphic signs!\n\n'Only one in a hundred Egyptians can read,' Khaemwaset says. 'Scribes hold great power. We record history, law, religion, medicine. Without writing, knowledge dies with each generation. With it, wisdom lives forever.'",
