        "daily-life": {
            "id": "daily-life",
            "summary": "They explore what ordinary Egyptian life was like",
            "text": "Meru takes them to the bustling streets of a nearby town. 'The pyramids are impressive, but daily life is where culture truly lives.'\n\nThey see bakers pulling bread from clay ovens. Weavers creating linen from flax. Children playing with toys‚Äîwooden animals, leather balls, carved game pieces. Women wearing beautiful beaded jewelry and kohl eyeliner.\n\n'Our lives center on the Nile,' Meru explains. 'Every year it floods, depositing rich soil for farming. We grow wheat, barley, vegetables, fruit. The river gives us fish, water for irrigation, and highways for travel.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} watches a scribe recording grain shipments. 'What do people do for fun?'\n\n'Music, dancing, board games‚ÄîSenet is very popular. Festivals for the gods happen throughout the year with feasting and celebrations. Hunting in the marshes. Swimming in the river‚Äîthough one must watch for crocodiles!'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} sees children attending a school, reciting lessons. 'Education?'\n\n'For those who will become scribes, priests, or officials, yes. Reading and writing open doors to power and wealth. A scribe can rise from poverty to advising Pharaoh himself.'",
