            "summary": "They realize hieroglyphics will be lost for centuries",
            "text": "{{PLAYER1_NAME}} thinks about something. 'In our time, people couldn't read hieroglyphics for over a thousand years. How did they figure it out?'\n\nKhaemwaset looks troubled. 'A thousand years of silence? How terrible. All this knowledge, lost?'\n\n'A stone was found,' {{PLAYER2_NAME}} remembers from school. 'The Rosetta Stone. It had the same message in hieroglyphics, another Egyptian script, and Greek. Since scholars could read Greek, they worked backward to crack the hieroglyphic code.'\n\n'A trilingual decree!' Khaemwaset nods approvingly. 'Clever. We make such documents‚Äîofficial announcements in multiple scripts so all can understand.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} realizes the importance. 'So writing in multiple languages actually saved your whole writing system from being lost forever.'\n\n'This is why scribes matter,' Khaemwaset says solemnly. 'We are the bridge between ages. What we record today, scholars in the distant future will read. Every document is a message in a bottle, cast into the sea of time.'",
