            "text": "The Great Sphinx is breathtaking‚Äîmuch more impressive than {{BOTH_NAMES}} expected. In this time, it's not weathered and sand-colored. It's freshly carved, painted in bright colors. Its face is vivid red, its headdress blue and gold.\n\n'The Guardian,' Meru says reverently. 'It has the body of a lion for strength and the face of Pharaoh for wisdom. It watches over the pyramid field, protecting it for eternity.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} stares up at the massive face. 'It looks so... young.'\n\n'It was carved from a single limestone outcrop. Some say it was already shaped like a lion's body by nature; we simply revealed the rest. Like how truth is already present, waiting to be uncovered.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} feels the scarab grow warm. 'Meru, the riddle on the scarab‚Äîabout Ra's journey. I think I'm starting to understand. Ra travels from east to west, dies each night, and is reborn each morning. It's about cycles, isn't it? Death isn't the end; it's part of a cycle.'\n\nMeru smiles. 'You are beginning to think like an Egyptian.'",
