        "sphinx-riddle": {
            "id": "sphinx-riddle",
            "summary": "The Sphinx speaks, posing a riddle about life's stages",
            "text": "As they approach the Sphinx's paws, something impossible happens. The stone face moves. Ancient eyes open and regard them.\n\n'YOUNG TRAVELERS,' a voice like grinding stone echoes. 'YOU HAVE LEARNED MUCH. BUT KNOWLEDGE WITHOUT WISDOM IS SAND THAT SLIPS THROUGH FINGERS. ANSWER MY RIDDLE, AND YOUR PATH HOME WILL BE REVEALED.'\n\n{{BOTH_NAMES}} exchange nervous glances. Even Meru looks awed.\n\n'WHAT WALKS ON FOUR LEGS IN THE MORNING, TWO LEGS AT NOON, AND THREE LEGS IN THE EVENING?'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}}'s brow furrows in thought. Morning... noon... evening... could it be a day?\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} remembers something from mythology class. 'It's not about time of day literally. It's about stages of life! A baby crawls on four limbs. An adult walks on two legs. An elderly person uses a cane‚Äîthree legs!'\n\n'THE ANSWER IS HUMAN,' {{PLAYER2_NAME}} says confidently.\n\nThe Sphinx's stone lips curve into the faintest smile. 'CORRECT. YOU UNDERSTAND THAT LIFE IS A JOURNEY WITH STAGES. SO TOO IS DEATH NOT AN END, BUT ANOTHER STAGE. YOU HAVE EARNED YOUR PASSAGE HOME.'",
