        "seek-return": {
            "id": "seek-return",
            "summary": "They ask Meru how to use the scarab to return home",
            "text": "'How do we get back to our own time?' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} asks Meru.\n\n'The scarab brought you here to learn. Once you understand its lesson, it will take you back.' Meru examines the amulet thoughtfully. 'What have you discovered about our way of seeing the world?'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} thinks back over everything. 'That you saw death as part of a journey, not the end. That the sun's daily cycle was a symbol of rebirth. That preserving knowledge‚Äîthrough writing, through building, through mummies‚Äîwas sacred because it defeated time.'\n\n'And what does that mean for you, in your time?'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} understands now. 'That what we create and learn can outlast us. That we're connected to everyone who came before and everyone who comes after. That knowledge passed down through generations is a kind of immortality.'\n\nMeru nods approvingly. 'The Sphinx guards not just tombs but wisdom. Perhaps it will confirm you are ready to return.'",
